Tracking Our Current State in the Seasons¶

What if instead of estimating how likely it is to rain today, we wanted to know how likely it is to rain on any given day this season?¶

In [12]:

rain_data=np.concatenate([np.random.choice([0,1], p=[.4, .6], replace=True, size=91),np.random.choice([0,1], p=[.9, .1], replace=True, size=91),
                                           np.random.choice([0,1], p=[.75, .25], replace=True, size=91), np.random.choice([0,1], p=[.1, .9], replace=True, size=92)])

plt.legend(fontsize=15,bbox_to_anchor=(1, .9) )

Out[12]:
Text(0, 0.5, 'Probility')

r = probability of rain this season¶

y = past observations of rain¶

cs = change in season¶

d = current day¶

Posterior belief in seasonal rain probbility¶

$$p(r_d|, y_{1:d}, cs) \propto p(y_{1:d}|r_{1:d})p(r| y_{1:d-1},cs)$$¶

Prior belief update on "rainy day" can "change season"¶

Note that this satisfies the markov property

$$p(r_d, cs| y_{1:d}) = {p(y_d|r_d)p(r_d,cs|y_{1:d-1}) \over \int \int p(y_d|r_d)p(r_d,cs|y_{1:d-1}) dr dcs}$$¶

Transition function from season to season¶

$$p(r_d|, y_{1:d-1}) = \int [p(r_{d-1}|y_{1:d-1}) * (1-cs_d)] + [1-p(r_{d-1}|y_{1:d-1}) * (cs_d)] dcs_d$$¶

class contingency_learner:

    '''Bayesian contingency learner'''
    def __init__(self, change_space=np.arange(0.01,0.21, .01), probability_space=np.arange(0.01,1, .01), transition_function='jumper',
                          n_trials=160):
        
        '''    
        change_space (array): possible values for change probability
        probability_space (array): possible values for contingency/association 
        transtion_function (string): type of transition function to be used
        n_trials (int): number of observation for the learner
        
        '''

        self.change_space=change_space
        self.probability_space=probability_space
        self.pspace_size, self.rspace_size = len(probability_space), len(change_space)
        
        #this is just for internl tracking
        self.trial_number=0

        if n_trials<1:
            raise Exception("Number of trials must be greater than 0")
        else:
            self.n_trials=n_trials

        if transition_function=='reversal':
            self.transition_func=(np.reshape(np.repeat(np.eye(self.pspace_size),self.rspace_size),(self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size,self.rspace_size))\
            * np.transpose(np.reshape(np.tile(1-self.change_space,(self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size)).transpose(),(self.rspace_size,self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size)),axes=[1, 2 ,0]))\
            + (np.reshape(np.repeat(np.fliplr(np.eye(self.pspace_size)),self.rspace_size),(self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size,self.rspace_size))\
            * np.transpose(np.reshape(np.tile(self.change_space,(self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size)).transpose(),(self.rspace_size,self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size)),axes=[1, 2, 0]))  
        elif transition_function=='jumper':
            self.transition_func=(np.reshape(np.repeat(np.eye(self.pspace_size),self.rspace_size),(self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size,self.rspace_size))\
            * np.transpose(np.reshape(np.tile(1-self.change_space,(self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size)).transpose(),(self.rspace_size,self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size)),axes=[1, 2 ,0]))\
            + ((np.ones((self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size,self.rspace_size))/self.pspace_size)\
            * np.transpose(np.reshape(np.tile(self.change_space,(self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size)).transpose(),(self.rspace_size,self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size)),axes=[1, 2, 0]))
        else: 
            raise Exception("Only 'jumper' and 'reversal' transitions allowed at this time")

        self.probability_space_2d,self.change_space_2d= np.meshgrid(self.probability_space,self.change_space, indexing='ij');
        self.prior_matrix_ps_given_rs=np.empty((self.probability_space_2d.shape[0],self.probability_space_2d.shape[1],n_trials))
        self.posterior_matrix_ps_given_rs=np.empty((self.probability_space_2d.shape[0],self.probability_space_2d.shape[1],n_trials))

        #creates uniform prior for the first trials
        self.prior_matrix_ps_given_rs[:,:,0]=np.ones(self.probability_space_2d.shape)/self.probability_space_2d.flatten().shape
#         self.marginalized_probability=np.empty((160,self.probability_space_2d.shape[0]))
#         self.marginalized_reversal=np.empty((160,self.change_space_2d.shape[1]))

    
    def update_beliefs(self, observation):
        
        if observation==1:
    #       if y(iTr) is a hit, p(y(iTr)|pS1) is simply pS1
            prob_of_observation_g_pS1pR=self.probability_space_2d;
        elif observation==0:
            prob_of_observation_g_pS1pR=1-self.probability_space_2d;
            
        #this is basically the entire bayesian part
        self.posterior_matrix_ps_given_rs[:,:,self.trial_number]=prob_of_observation_g_pS1pR*self.prior_matrix_ps_given_rs[:,:,self.trial_number];
        self.posterior_matrix_ps_given_rs[:,:,self.trial_number]=self.posterior_matrix_ps_given_rs[:,:,self.trial_number]/np.sum(np.sum(self.posterior_matrix_ps_given_rs[:,:,self.trial_number]));
        
        #apply transition function at the end of the trial
        unpacked_post_S1=np.transpose(np.reshape(np.repeat(self.posterior_matrix_ps_given_rs[:,:,self.trial_number],
                                                            self.pspace_size),( self.pspace_size, self.rspace_size, self.pspace_size)),axes=[0, 2, 1])
        unpacked_prior_S1=unpacked_post_S1*self.transition_func;
        
        if self.trial_number+1<self.n_trials:
            self.prior_matrix_ps_given_rs[:,:,self.trial_number+1]=np.squeeze(np.sum(unpacked_prior_S1,0))
            self.prior_matrix_ps_given_rs[:,:,self.trial_number+1]=self.prior_matrix_ps_given_rs[:,:,self.trial_number+1]/np.sum(np.sum(self.prior_matrix_ps_given_rs[:,:,self.trial_number+1]))
        else:
            pass
        
        self.trial_number+=1
    
    def get_marginal_points(self, axis='contingencies'):
        
        if axis=='contingencies':
            marginals=np.transpose(np.squeeze(np.sum(self.prior_matrix_ps_given_rs, 1)))
            marginal_points=np.matmul(marginals, self.probability_space )
        else:
            marginals=np.transpose(np.squeeze(np.sum(self.prior_matrix_ps_given_rs, 0)))
            marginal_points=np.matmul(marginals, self.change_space )
        
        return marginal_points
    
    def get_marginal_distribution(self, axis='contingencies'):
        
        if axis=='contingencies':
            marginals=np.transpose(np.squeeze(np.sum(self.prior_matrix_ps_given_rs, 1)))
        else:
            marginals=np.transpose(np.squeeze(np.sum(self.prior_matrix_ps_given_rs, 0)))
        
        return marginals

    def get_information_update(self, func_type='_kl_divergence'):
        
        prior_marginals=np.transpose(np.squeeze(np.sum(self.prior_matrix_ps_given_rs, 1)))
        posterior_marginals=np.transpose(np.squeeze(np.sum(self.posterior_matrix_ps_given_rs, 1)))
        dkl=np.empty((prior_marginals.shape[0]))
        info_function=getattr(self, func_type)
        
        for i in range(prior_marginals.shape[0]):
            dkl[i]=info_function(prior_marginals[i,:], posterior_marginals[i,:])
        return dkl
    
    def _kl_divergence(self, p, q):
        return sum(p *np.log2(p/q))
    
    def _js_divergence(self, p, q):
        mean=(p+q)/2
        return (self._kl_diveregence(p, mean) + self._kl_diveregence(q, mean))/2

class variance_learner:
    
    def __init__(self, max_sigma=80, volitility_bins=24, transition_function='jumper',
                          n_trials=160):
        
        self.sigma_p=np.arange(2, max_sigma, 1)
        self.change_space=1/np.arange(1,500,500/volitility_bins) 
        
        self.pspace_size, self.rspace_size = len(self.sigma_p), len(self.change_space)

        #this is just for internl tracking
        self.trial_number=0

        if n_trials<1:
            raise Exception("Number of trials must be greater than 0")
        else:
            self.n_trials=n_trials

        if transition_function=='reversal':
            self.transition_func=(np.reshape(np.repeat(np.eye(self.pspace_size),self.rspace_size),(self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size,self.rspace_size))\
            * np.transpose(np.reshape(np.tile(1-self.change_space,(self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size)).transpose(),(self.rspace_size,self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size)),axes=[1, 2 ,0]))\
            + (np.reshape(np.repeat(np.fliplr(np.eye(self.pspace_size)),self.rspace_size),(self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size,self.rspace_size))\
            * np.transpose(np.reshape(np.tile(self.change_space,(self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size)).transpose(),(self.rspace_size,self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size)),axes=[1, 2, 0]))  
        elif transition_function=='jumper':
            self.transition_func=(np.reshape(np.repeat(np.eye(self.pspace_size),self.rspace_size),(self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size,self.rspace_size))\
            * np.transpose(np.reshape(np.tile(1-self.change_space,(self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size)).transpose(),(self.rspace_size,self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size)),axes=[1, 2 ,0]))\
            + ((np.ones((self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size,self.rspace_size))/self.pspace_size)\
            * np.transpose(np.reshape(np.tile(self.change_space,(self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size)).transpose(),(self.rspace_size,self.pspace_size,self.pspace_size)),axes=[1, 2, 0]))
        else: 
            raise Exception("Only 'jumper' and 'reversal' transitions allowed at this time")

        
     
        self.sigma_2d, self.change_2d=np.meshgrid(self.sigma_p, self.change_space, indexing='ij')
        self.prior_matrix_sig_given_rs=np.empty((self.sigma_2d.shape[0],self.sigma_2d.shape[1],n_trials))
        self.posterior_matrix_sig_given_rs=np.empty((self.sigma_2d.shape[0],self.sigma_2d.shape[1],n_trials))

        #creates uniform prior for the first trials
        #self.prior_matrix_sig_given_rs[:,:,0]=np.ones(self.sigma_2d.shape)/self.sigma_2d.flatten().shape
        prior_gamma_dist=sts.gamma(a=2, scale=5).pdf(self.sigma_p)
        prior_gamma_dist=prior_gamma_dist/sum(prior_gamma_dist)
        self.prior_matrix_sig_given_rs[:,:,0]=np.reshape(np.repeat(prior_gamma_dist,24),self.sigma_2d.shape)*self.change_2d
        
        self.marginalized_probability=np.empty((160,self.sigma_2d.shape[0]))
        self.marginalized_reversal=np.empty((160,self.sigma_2d.shape[1]))

        
    def update_beliefs(self, observation):
        
        prob_of_observation_g_sigma=sts.norm.pdf(loc=0,scale=self.sigma_2d, x=observation)

            
        #this is basically the entire bayesian part
        self.posterior_matrix_sig_given_rs[:,:,self.trial_number]=prob_of_observation_g_sigma*self.prior_matrix_sig_given_rs[:,:,self.trial_number];
        self.posterior_matrix_sig_given_rs[:,:,self.trial_number]=self.posterior_matrix_sig_given_rs[:,:,self.trial_number]/np.sum(np.sum(self.posterior_matrix_sig_given_rs[:,:,self.trial_number]));
        
        #apply transition function at the end of the trial
        unpacked_post_S1=np.transpose(np.reshape(np.repeat(self.posterior_matrix_sig_given_rs[:,:,self.trial_number],
                                                            self.pspace_size),( self.pspace_size, self.rspace_size, self.pspace_size)),axes=[0, 2, 1])
        unpacked_prior_S1=unpacked_post_S1*self.transition_func;
        
        if self.trial_number+1<self.n_trials:
            self.prior_matrix_sig_given_rs[:,:,self.trial_number+1]=np.squeeze(np.sum(unpacked_prior_S1,0))
            self.prior_matrix_sig_given_rs[:,:,self.trial_number+1]=self.prior_matrix_sig_given_rs[:,:,self.trial_number+1]/np.sum(np.sum(self.prior_matrix_sig_given_rs[:,:,self.trial_number+1]))
        else:
            pass
        
        self.trial_number+=1
    
    def get_marginal_points(self, axis='sigmas'):
        
        if axis=='sigmas':
            marginals=np.transpose(np.squeeze(np.sum(self.prior_matrix_sig_given_rs, 1)))
            marginal_points=np.matmul(marginals, self.sigma_p )
        else:
            marginals=np.transpose(np.squeeze(np.sum(self.posterior_matrix_sig_given_rs, 0)))
            marginal_points=np.matmul(marginals, self.sigma_p )
        
        return marginal_points
    
    def get_marginal_distribution(self, axis='sigmas'):
        
        if axis=='sigmas':
            marginals=np.transpose(np.squeeze(np.sum(self.prior_matrix_sig_given_rs, 1)))
        else:
            marginals=np.transpose(np.squeeze(np.sum(self.prior_matrix_sig_given_rs, 0)))
        
        return marginals
    def get_information_update(self, func_type='_kl_divergence'):
        
        prior_marginals=np.transpose(np.squeeze(np.sum(self.prior_matrix_sig_given_rs, 1)))
        posterior_marginals=np.transpose(np.squeeze(np.sum(self.posterior_matrix_sig_given_rs, 1)))
        dkl=np.empty((prior_marginals.shape[0]))
        info_function=getattr(self, func_type)
        
        for i in range(prior_marginals.shape[0]):
            dkl[i]=info_function(prior_marginals[i,:], posterior_marginals[i,:])
        return dkl
    
    def _kl_divergence(self, p, q):
        return sum(p *np.log2(p/q))
    
    def _js_divergence(self, p, q):
        mean=(p+q)/2
        return (self._kl_diveregence(p, mean) + self._kl_diveregence(q, mean))/2

#belief in what they knew before encoding/sampling object features
uniform_belief=np.ones(360)/360

# what they could know if they encode/sample each object feature
color_belief_after_observation=sts.truncnorm(-180, 180, loc=0, scale=color_belief).pdf(np.arange(-180, 180, 1))
color_belief_after_observation=color_belief_after_observation/np.sum(color_belief_after_observation)


orientation_belief_after_observation=sts.truncnorm(-180, 180, loc=0, scale=orientation_belief).pdf(np.arange(-180, 180, 1))
orientation_belief_after_observation=orientation_belief_after_observation/np.sum(orientation_belief_after_observation)
  
# calcualte information gain
color_kl=color_learner._kl_divergence(uniform_belief, color_belief_after_observation)
orientation_kl=color_learner._kl_divergence(uniform_belief, orientation_belief_after_observation)
